            "id": "e41f133c5a934fd58f263",
            "questionText": "A nuclear power plant operates continuously at a thermal power of 3000 MW and converts 35% of this thermal power into electricity. It produces 20 cubic meters of high-level radioactive waste per year. Calculate the current volume of high-level radioactive waste produced per megawatt-hour (MWh) of electricity generated.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "2221043ba1234996a47b6",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by calculating the electrical power output from the thermal power using the given conversion efficiency. Identify the correct relation to compute the electrical power from the thermal power and efficiency.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "1050"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "MW",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P_e = efficiency \\times P_{th}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P_e = P_{th} / efficiency$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$P_e = efficiency + P_{th}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "cb8e163f36a34082a456a",
                    "stepText": "Great, now using the calculated electrical power output, compute the total annual electrical energy generated. Multiply the electrical power by the total hours in a year. Please choose the correct formula that relates power, time, and energy.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "9198000"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "MWh",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$Energy = P_e \\times t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$Energy = P_e / t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$Energy = t / P_e$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "fdd6484ae7844cdbbfc83",
                    "stepText": "Finally, determine how much waste is produced per MWh of electricity by dividing the total annual radioactive waste volume by the annual energy production. Identify the correct expression for this relation.",
